@@TJvListbox2.DeleteAllButSelected
Description:
Call this method to remove all selected items of the list. If the MultiSelect property is false, the method does nothing.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvListbox2.DeleteExactString@string@Boolean@Boolean
Description:
Call this method to delete a string of the list. This method can either delete all or only the first occurence of the string.

Parameters:
Value: 
is the string you want to search for.
All: 
is true if you want to delete all occurences of the string
CaseSensitive:
is true if the search is case sensitive, false if not.

Returns:
X the index of the item in the list. 

-1 if the string hasn't been found.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvListbox2.DeleteSelected
Description:
Call this method to remove all selected items of the list. If the MultiSelect property is false, it deletes the item indexed by the ItemIndex property.

