@@TJvListbox2.SearchExactString@string@Boolean
Description:
Call this method to search an exact string in the list.

Parameters:
Value: 
is the string you want to search for.
CaseSensitive: 
is true if the search is case sensitive, false if not.

Returns:
X the index of the item in the list. 

-1 if the string hasn't been found.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvListbox2.SearchPrefix@string@Boolean
Description:
Call this method to search a prefix in the list. A prefix is the beginning of the word (ex "Cas" is a prefix for "CaseSensitive").

Parameters:
Value: 
is the string you want to search for.
CaseSensitive:
is true if the search is case sensitive, false if not.

Returns:
X the index of the item in the list. 

-1 if the string hasn't been found.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvListbox2.SearchSubString@string@Boolean
Description:
Call this method to search a substring in the list. A substring is string contained in a string (ex "ens" is a substring of "CaseSensitive").

Parameters:
Value: 
is the string you want to search for.
CaseSensitive: 
is true if the search is case sensitive, false if not.

Returns:
X the index of the item in the list. 

-1 if the string hasn't been found.

